-- TPG Capital, Carlyle Name Banks For Healthscope Hybrid Debt, Review Says
-- B y   T i m   S m i t h
-- 2010-10-11T19:58:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/tpg-capital-carlyle-name-banks-for-healthscope-hybrid-debt-review-says.html
TPG Capital and The Carlyle Group
named five banks to manage the A$200 million hybrid securities
issue to help fund the purchase of Healthscope Ltd., the
Australian Financial Review reported in its Street Talk column,
without saying where it got the information. Australia & New
Zealand Banking Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG Macquarie
Group Ltd., UBS AG and Westpac Banking Corp. won the mandate for
the notes, which are expected to be priced at 550 basis points
to 600 basis points more than the 180-day bank bill swap rate,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tim Smith in Sydney at 
